<h2 id="Syntax" name="Syntax">Syntax</h2>

<pre class="twopartsyntaxbox"><a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax" title="CSS/Value_definition_syntax">Formal syntax</a>: <code><a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length" title="Possible values: a number followed by'em', 'ex', 'ch', 'rem', 'px', 'cm', 'mm', 'in', 'vh', 'vw', 'vmin', 'vmax', 'pt', 'pc' or 'px', like 3px, 1.5cm, -0.5em or 0">&lt;length&gt;</a> <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#Single_bar" title="Single bar: The two entities are optional, but exactly one must be present.">|</a> normal</code>
</pre>

<pre>column-gap: 3px
column-gap: 2.5em
column-gap: normal

column-gap: inherit
</pre>

<h3 id="Values">Values</h3>

<dl><dt><code>normal</code></dt>
 <dd>Is a keyword indicating to use the browser-defined default spacing between columns. The specification, and most modern browsers follow it, recommends this keyword to be equal to a length of <code>1em</code>.</dd>
 <dt><code>&lt;length&gt;</code></dt>
 <dd>Is a <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length" title="The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!"><code>&lt;length&gt;</code></a> value defining the size of the gap between columns. It must not be negative, but may be equal to <code>0</code>.</dd>
</dl>